  "title": "accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain full set of accounts and ensure timely, accurate month-end closing and forecast in accordance to IFRS accounting standards</li>\n  <li>Handle day to day account operations and be responsible for accounting processes and tasks</li>\n  <li>Responsible for preparation of monthly management reports including the current month's closing results and 3-month forecast</li>\n  <li>Reconcile intercompany balances/transactions and ensure account</li>\n  <li>reconciliations are performed and reviewed</li>\n  <li>Prepare weekly cashflow report, bank reconciliation and journal entries</li>\n  <li>Handle tax annual filing</li>\n  <li>Prepare GST submission and tax filing</li>\n  <li>Assist in new processes and system implementation to enhance efficiency and effectiveness.</li>\n  <li>Handling bank account opening</li>\n  <li>Any other tasks as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Knowledge, Skills &amp; Abilities</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Accounting/Finance/Commerce.</li>\n  <li>Experience in project costing and accruals</li>\n  <li>Team player with confidence and maturity to work efficiently with different levels in the organization.</li>\n  <li>Hands-on with Microsoft office applications.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with accounting software (e.g., Xero, QuickBooks, or similar).</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently.</li>\n  <li>Fluency in both spoken and written Chinese and English is required. The candidate must be able to speak      Mandarin for communication with stakeholders and teams in China.</li>\n</ul>",
